Terminal commands:

Launch PostgreSQL terminal - psql

Copy table from one db to another - pg_dump -t table_name copyfrom_db_name | psql copyto_db_name

&nbsp;

PSQL commands:

List databases - \d

List tables in current database - \dt

List table structure - \d table_name

List table contents - TABLE table_name;

Connect to a different database - \c database_name

